Ext.data.JsonP['Viewing_Custom_Cloud_Services']({"guide":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n    <title>Viewing Custom Cloud Services</title>\n\n    <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n    <meta content=\"Scroll EclipseHelp Exporter\" name=\"generator\">\n\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"print\">\n</link></link></link></meta></meta></head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n\t\t<div id=\"banner\" class=\"confbox admonition admonition-note aui-message warning shadowed information-macro\">\n\t\t\t<p>You can now find Appcelerator documentation at <a href=\"https://docs.axway.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://docs.axway.com/</a>. This site will be taken down in the near future.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n        <div class=\"header\"/>\n\n        <div id=\"src-43298788\" class=\"content\">\n                        <h1>Viewing Custom Cloud Services</h1>\n    <p>    </p>\n<ul class=\"toc-indentation \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Viewing_Custom_Cloud_Services-section-src-43298788_ViewingCustomCloudServices-APIBuilderAPIcallsmetricdetailsscreen\">API Builder API calls metric details screen</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Viewing_Custom_Cloud_Services-section-src-43298788_ViewingCustomCloudServices-APIBuilderapplicationdetailsscreen\">API Builder application details screen</a>    </p>\n<ul class=\"toc-indentation \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Viewing_Custom_Cloud_Services-section-src-43298788_ViewingCustomCloudServices-Overview\">Overview</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Viewing_Custom_Cloud_Services-section-src-43298788_ViewingCustomCloudServices-Logs\">Logs</a>    </p>\n</li></ul></li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Viewing_Custom_Cloud_Services-section-src-43298788_ViewingCustomCloudServices-ViewingAPIBuilderapplicationsusedbyaclientapplication\">Viewing API Builder applications used by a client application</a>    </p>\n</li></ul>    <p>If you created an API Builder application and associated it with your organization, or the client application makes requests to an API Builder application using the Titanium HTTP client, you can view information about the API Builder application in Dashboard.  To associate an API Builder application with a client application built with Java or Objective-C, you need to add <tt class=\" \">x-native-id</tt> header to the HTTP request as instructed in <a class=\"document-link unresolved\" href=\"#!/guide/Viewing_Custom_Cloud_Services-section-src-43298788\">Associate API Builder Applications with Client Applications</a>.    </p>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-43298788_ViewingCustomCloudServices-APIBuilderAPIcallsmetricdetailsscreen\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>API Builder  API calls metric details screen</span></h2>\n    <p>To view aggregate data about all your organization&apos;s API Builder applications, from the <strong class=\" \">Dashboard Home</strong> screen or the <strong class=\" \">Metric Details</strong> screen, click on the <strong class=\" \">Metric Details</strong> drop-down and select <strong class=\" \">Cloud API Calls (Custom)</strong>.    </p>\n    <p>    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298788/MetricDetailsDropDown.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298788/MetricDetailsDropDown.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border\">\n        </img></p>\n    <p>The Cloud API Calls (Custom) metric details page opens.  This page displays data about all of your organization&apos;s API Builder applications, such as total API calls to the application, CPU usage, memory usage and number of Titanium client applications making calls to the API Builder application.    </p>\n    <p>    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298788/NodeACSAPICall.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298788/NodeACSAPICall.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border\">\n        </img></p>\n    <p>Click on a Service Name to view more details about the API Builder application.    </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-43298788_ViewingCustomCloudServices-APIBuilderapplicationdetailsscreen\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>API Builder  application details screen</span></h2>\n    <p>When you select an API Builder application in either the client application&apos;s Cloud Custom Service tab or Cloud API Calls (Custom) metric details page, its details are displayed in a new page.  From the details screen, you can view basic information about the application and a log of API calls made to the application.    </p>\n    <div class=\"section section-3 \" id=\"src-43298788_ViewingCustomCloudServices-Overview\">\n        <h3 class=\"heading \"><span>Overview</span></h3>\n    <p>Click on the <strong class=\" \">Overview</strong> button to view basic information about the application.  This page displays:    </p>\n<ul class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>The endpoint URL to access the application    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Creation and last published date of the application    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Total API calls made to the application    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Number of cloud containers used by the application    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Overall CPU and memory usage and also broken down by cloud containers    </p>\n</li></ul>    <p>If you are an organization administrator, you can also see a list of the connected client applications using the API Builder application.  Click on the application name to open the application&apos;s Cloud Custom Services tab.    </p>\n    <p>    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298788/NodeACSOverviewTab.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298788/NodeACSOverviewTab.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border\">\n        </img></p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-3 \" id=\"src-43298788_ViewingCustomCloudServices-Logs\">\n        <h3 class=\"heading \"><span>Logs</span></h3>\n    <p>Click the Logs button to display a list of API calls made to the application.  Each entry in the log lists the URL path, response time, remote IP that made the call, the cloud container that handled the call, and the datetime of the request.    </p>\n    <p>    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298788/NodeACSLogsTab.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298788/NodeACSLogsTab.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border\">\n        </img></p>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-43298788_ViewingCustomCloudServices-ViewingAPIBuilderapplicationsusedbyaclientapplication\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Viewing  API Builder  applications used by a client application</span></h2>\n    <p>From the Application Details screen, you can view the API Builder applications the client application is using.  To view the list:    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>Select the application from the <strong class=\" \">Apps</strong> menu.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click the <strong class=\" \">Cloud</strong> tab.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click the <strong class=\" \">Custom Services</strong> sub-tab.    </p>\n</li></ol>    <p>Click on a Service Name to view more details about the API Builder application.    </p>\n    <p>    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298788/ApplicationDetailsCustomServices.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298788/ApplicationDetailsCustomServices.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n        </img></p>\n    <p>    </p>\n    </div>\n        </div><a id=\"editButton\" href=\"https://wiki.appcelerator.org/pages/editpage.action?pageId=43298788\"><span>Edit</span></a>\n    \n        \n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","title":"Viewing Custom Cloud Services"});